WEBVTT

00:01.402 --> 00:03.771
MITCH: A year ago,
the animals started acting strangely,

00:03.804 --> 00:04.705
but no one noticed...

00:04.738 --> 00:05.439
(growling)

00:05.473 --> 00:06.674
until they began attacking,

00:06.707 --> 00:08.442
coordinating,

00:08.476 --> 00:09.477
evolving.

00:09.510 --> 00:11.345
The animals were mutating,

00:11.379 --> 00:13.190
and it was happening faster
than anyone expected.

00:13.214 --> 00:14.082
(screams)

00:14.115 --> 00:16.484
The government came
up with a plan.

00:16.517 --> 00:17.594
PSA NARRATOR: Thanks
to the Noah Objective,

00:17.618 --> 00:18.686
in six to ten years

00:18.719 --> 00:20.321
the world's animal population

00:20.354 --> 00:22.623
will be thriving once again.

00:22.656 --> 00:24.558
Killing the animals?
Play God and repopulate

00:24.592 --> 00:25.693
the planet?

00:25.726 --> 00:27.128
This is ridiculous.

00:27.161 --> 00:28.662
MITCH: But messing
with Mother Nature

00:28.696 --> 00:30.464
could be catastrophic.

00:30.498 --> 00:33.401
So a group of us are
trying to save the animals.

00:33.434 --> 00:35.469
Jackson Oz and Abraham Kenyatta,

00:35.503 --> 00:37.071
animal experts.

00:37.105 --> 00:38.339
Chloe Tousignant,

00:38.372 --> 00:39.607
an intel operative.

00:39.640 --> 00:41.375
Jamie Campbell,

00:41.409 --> 00:43.111
a reporter who's been

00:43.144 --> 00:44.154
following this story, found me,

00:44.178 --> 00:45.379
Mitch Morgan,

00:45.413 --> 00:47.348
a veterinary pathologist.

00:48.482 --> 00:49.783
We thought all hope was lost

00:49.817 --> 00:51.485
when the key to our cure

00:51.519 --> 00:52.453
crashed and burned...

00:52.486 --> 00:53.354
but we were wrong.

00:53.387 --> 00:55.089
I still have it.

00:55.123 --> 00:56.400
I have the leopard,
I have the cure.

00:56.424 --> 00:59.093
Now we just have to get to Jamie

00:59.127 --> 01:00.704
and the leopard,
but time is running out.

01:00.728 --> 01:01.795
(bats screeching)

01:06.400 --> 01:07.335
What's the plan?

01:07.368 --> 01:09.370
There's a boat that
will take us to Jamie.

01:09.403 --> 01:10.471
A boat?

01:10.504 --> 01:11.805
It'll take 18 hours or so,

01:11.839 --> 01:13.374
but, you know, air travel.

01:13.407 --> 01:18.512
Yeah, I'm okay not getting
on a plane for a while.

01:18.546 --> 01:19.647
Hey.

01:19.680 --> 01:21.515
What is that?

01:21.549 --> 01:22.650
You all right?

01:22.683 --> 01:24.218
Oh, yeah, yeah,
yeah, it's nothing.

01:24.252 --> 01:25.553
It's a dog bite, it's fine.

01:25.586 --> 01:27.688
That needs to be cleaned up.

01:27.721 --> 01:29.257
It doesn't look too good.

01:29.290 --> 01:30.558
Will do.

01:30.591 --> 01:32.393
(elephant trumpets)

01:33.394 --> 01:35.696
What the hell?

01:35.729 --> 01:36.840
This doesn't look so
good, either.

01:36.864 --> 01:39.433
(roars)

01:42.503 --> 01:45.539
(growling)

01:46.707 --> 01:48.542
Any ideas?

01:48.576 --> 01:50.511
I'm open to suggestions.

01:50.544 --> 01:51.645
(growling)

01:51.679 --> 01:52.689
Yeah, man, get us out of here.

01:52.713 --> 01:53.814
Hold on.

01:53.847 --> 01:55.516
(tires screeching)

02:00.388 --> 02:01.388
Turn here!

02:02.590 --> 02:05.326
ABRAHAM: We need
to get to Jamie.

02:05.359 --> 02:06.427
And the cure.

02:06.460 --> 02:07.595
(Chloe shouts)

02:07.628 --> 02:09.297
(rhinoceros groans)

02:22.543 --> 02:23.577
We got to keep moving.

02:23.611 --> 02:25.779
If the harbor's
anything like this,

02:25.813 --> 02:26.856
the captain won't wait long.

02:26.880 --> 02:29.750
(elephant trumpets)

02:29.783 --> 02:30.818
Neither will they.

02:35.556 --> 02:37.191
Abe.

02:37.225 --> 02:38.859
Count to five, light me.

02:38.892 --> 02:40.594
What are you doing?

02:40.628 --> 02:42.596
I'm making a wall. Meet me at.

02:42.630 --> 02:43.707
Amelia's office, she'll get us

02:43.731 --> 02:44.765
another car.

02:44.798 --> 02:45.599
Are you out of your mind?

02:45.633 --> 02:47.535
Probably.

02:47.568 --> 02:48.612
(lion roars and
elephant trumpets)

02:48.636 --> 02:50.404
Oh, boy.

02:59.447 --> 03:00.648
Let's go. CHLOE: No!

03:00.681 --> 03:02.550
We can't just leave him.
He said he'll

03:02.583 --> 03:04.618
meet us at Amelia's
office and he will.

03:04.652 --> 03:05.185
No. He's an African

03:05.219 --> 03:05.886
safari guide; I like his

03:05.919 --> 03:07.187
chances way better than ours.

03:26.740 --> 03:28.742
(tiger roars)

03:29.743 --> 03:31.679
(growling)

03:35.048 --> 03:37.251
(bees buzzing)

03:38.819 --> 03:39.720
MITCH: Run, Chloe.

03:39.753 --> 03:40.721
Guys.

03:40.754 --> 03:42.556
ABRAHAM: Go, go, go!

03:45.759 --> 03:47.261
(baby crying)

03:47.295 --> 03:48.696
WOMAN: Help.

03:48.729 --> 03:50.731
Help!

03:51.799 --> 03:53.834
(baby crying)

03:53.867 --> 03:54.935
Save my baby.

03:54.968 --> 03:57.605
Please help.

03:57.638 --> 03:58.639
Take her.

03:58.672 --> 03:59.640
(baby crying)

03:59.673 --> 04:01.642
I got her.

04:01.675 --> 04:04.011
(baby crying)

04:08.749 --> 04:10.651
(people screaming)

04:10.684 --> 04:12.753
(indistinct radio transmission)

04:12.786 --> 04:13.954
(sirens wailing)

04:13.987 --> 04:14.998
MAN (over P.A.): New arrivals

04:15.022 --> 04:16.957
without family members...

04:16.990 --> 04:18.559
MITCH: Hey.

04:18.591 --> 04:21.329
Hey, uh, we're-we're
here to see Amelia Sage.

04:21.362 --> 04:23.006
And we're looking for Chloe
Tousignant and Jackson Oz.

04:23.030 --> 04:24.532
Have they checked in yet?

04:24.565 --> 04:26.300
Couldn't tell you, pal,
we're a little busy.

04:26.334 --> 04:27.301
(sighs)

04:27.335 --> 04:28.936
I can't see them anywhere.

04:28.969 --> 04:31.772
The National Guard struggles
to regain control of the city

04:31.805 --> 04:33.774
from the escaped zoo animals.

04:33.807 --> 04:38.479
The death toll continues to
rise with 362 known fatalities

04:38.512 --> 04:41.382
and thousands injured
in what many are calling

04:41.415 --> 04:42.483
the Day of the Beast.

04:42.516 --> 04:43.851
MITCH: Chloe!

04:43.884 --> 04:45.018
Hey.

04:45.052 --> 04:46.487
Where's Jackson?

04:46.520 --> 04:47.488
We hoped he was here.

04:47.521 --> 04:48.589
Why do you have a baby?

04:48.622 --> 04:49.699
It happened after the hornets.

04:49.723 --> 04:51.859
A mother, she...

04:51.892 --> 04:53.661
sh-she, she didn't survive.

04:53.694 --> 04:55.563
That's terrible. MITCH: Yeah.

04:55.596 --> 04:57.665
This day's chock-full
of terrible.

04:57.698 --> 04:58.875
Hopefully Amelia can salvage it.

04:58.899 --> 05:00.368
Find us a way out of town.

05:00.401 --> 05:01.769
She hasn't

05:01.802 --> 05:03.671
checked in yet. Jackson!

05:04.705 --> 05:05.706
Hey.

05:05.739 --> 05:06.707
What happened to you?

05:06.740 --> 05:07.975
You okay?

05:08.008 --> 05:09.577
Yeah, yeah, I'm fine.

05:09.610 --> 05:10.844
I'm fine.

05:12.680 --> 05:15.983
Rafiki, what happened out there?

05:17.851 --> 05:19.052
Brakes failed.

05:19.086 --> 05:20.053
I had to jump but

05:20.087 --> 05:21.889
fire did the trick.

05:21.922 --> 05:23.424
Scared all the animals away?

05:23.457 --> 05:24.492
Yeah, didn't see any

05:24.525 --> 05:25.926
after the explosion.

05:25.959 --> 05:27.495
(tiger roars)

05:27.528 --> 05:31.098
(tiger growling)

05:39.807 --> 05:42.676
(tiger sniffing)

05:54.655 --> 05:56.857
Got lucky, I guess.

06:02.830 --> 06:05.933
â™ª

06:42.670 --> 06:44.672
(growls)

06:45.739 --> 06:47.575
My friends are coming to get us.

06:47.608 --> 06:49.843
You have a very
important job to do.

06:49.877 --> 06:51.178
(speaks Inuttitut)

06:51.211 --> 06:52.680
(laughs)

06:52.713 --> 06:54.081
You know, they are going

06:54.114 --> 06:56.049
to write books about
you, the man who saved

06:56.083 --> 06:57.685
the leopard who saved the world.

06:57.718 --> 06:58.952
I'm going to

06:58.986 --> 07:00.621
make sure that
they're translated.

07:00.654 --> 07:02.122
Nawok.

07:02.155 --> 07:03.557
Nawok?

07:03.591 --> 07:05.626
That's... uh, rope?

07:05.659 --> 07:08.629
(chuckles)

07:13.133 --> 07:14.802
(leopard growling)

07:14.835 --> 07:16.570
Hey.

07:16.604 --> 07:18.739
What is it?

07:18.772 --> 07:20.941
(whining)

07:20.974 --> 07:22.743
(screeches)

07:22.776 --> 07:26.614
Hey, there, little, uh...

07:26.647 --> 07:28.716
little gremlin guy.

07:28.749 --> 07:31.652
(chattering)

07:31.685 --> 07:34.655
How'd you get in here?

07:35.923 --> 07:37.758
(bear roaring)

07:37.791 --> 07:39.026
(Jamie shouts)

07:40.093 --> 07:41.829
(wolves growling)

07:44.765 --> 07:46.466
(bear roars)

07:52.840 --> 07:54.942
(growls)

08:04.718 --> 08:06.754
(wolves growling)

08:18.766 --> 08:20.568
(whines)

08:20.601 --> 08:21.911
WOMAN: You've lost
a lot of blood.

08:21.935 --> 08:24.037
Well,
then why are you taking more?

08:24.071 --> 08:25.773
Typing and crossing. All right.

08:25.806 --> 08:27.274
You may need a transfusion.

08:27.307 --> 08:28.275
I'm fine. Hey,

08:28.308 --> 08:29.977
she's just trying to help.

08:31.745 --> 08:33.746
I will save you the trouble.

08:33.780 --> 08:36.015
O-negative,
I'm a universal donor.

08:36.049 --> 08:37.059
Still got to check, handsome.

08:37.083 --> 08:38.193
You got banged up pretty good.

08:38.217 --> 08:39.186
May have internal bleeding.

08:39.219 --> 08:40.187
And what about

08:40.220 --> 08:41.621
his bite?

08:41.655 --> 08:42.623
Keep it clean.

08:42.655 --> 08:44.256
Watch for infection, and

08:44.291 --> 08:46.035
if you're wondering,
just like everyone else,

08:46.059 --> 08:47.671
the animals can't pass
the virus on to humans.

08:47.695 --> 08:49.196
It's not a virus.

08:49.229 --> 08:51.899
Whatever it is,
it's not contagious.

08:55.068 --> 08:56.036
You could have been killed.

08:56.069 --> 08:57.638
I wasn't, okay?

08:57.671 --> 08:59.006
And I'm not waiting around

08:59.039 --> 09:00.808
for some ridiculous
blood results.

09:00.841 --> 09:01.809
I'm fine.

09:01.842 --> 09:02.810
You're not fine.

09:02.843 --> 09:03.977
None of this is fine.

09:04.011 --> 09:05.713
Chloe, I'm okay.

09:05.746 --> 09:06.513
Everything's okay.

09:06.546 --> 09:08.048
Tell that to the
mother of this child

09:08.081 --> 09:09.316
or anyone else who died today.

09:09.349 --> 09:11.151
The sooner we get out of here,

09:11.184 --> 09:13.329
the sooner that we can get to
the leopard and find the cure,

09:13.353 --> 09:14.655
and everything will be okay.

09:14.688 --> 09:15.956
Yes, and what if it isn't?

09:15.989 --> 09:18.158
The mutation has
spread to insects.

09:18.191 --> 09:19.660
They were the dispersal method.

09:19.693 --> 09:21.070
Yeah, well,
that's still our best chance.

09:21.094 --> 09:23.330
It's time for a solution
we know will work.

09:26.066 --> 09:30.137
There are over 42 million
species of animal.

09:30.170 --> 09:31.672
Wreaking havoc on the world.

09:31.705 --> 09:33.182
So, you're in favor
of the Noah Objective

09:33.206 --> 09:34.675
now, huh? You want to

09:34.708 --> 09:35.843
call all the animals,

09:35.876 --> 09:37.878
exterminate them,
and then repopulate.

09:37.911 --> 09:40.313
If it means saving lives.
It is straight up murder.

09:40.347 --> 09:41.925
And what do you call what
happened to this child's mother?

09:41.949 --> 09:43.250
I call it terrible. Huh?

09:43.283 --> 09:44.718
It's terrible.

09:44.752 --> 09:45.795
After everything
we've been through,

09:45.819 --> 09:47.387
wasn't there a moment when

09:47.420 --> 09:49.733
you felt that putting a bullet
in them was the right thing?

09:49.757 --> 09:52.693
MITCH: Hey, Danny and Sandy.

09:52.726 --> 09:56.029
We finally got somebody from
Amelia's office to talk to us.

10:00.668 --> 10:02.369
Guys, this is Eleanor Lewis.

10:02.402 --> 10:04.204
She's with IADG.

10:04.237 --> 10:05.873
Okay. Where's Amelia?

10:05.906 --> 10:08.208
Her motorcade was attacked.

10:08.241 --> 10:09.777
There were no survivors.

10:09.810 --> 10:11.879
It's not just here.

10:11.912 --> 10:13.213
The animals have attacked

10:13.246 --> 10:15.916
Berlin, Moscow,
Paris, Hong Kong...

10:15.949 --> 10:17.885
MITCH: Not to make
bad news worse,

10:17.918 --> 10:21.889
but the mutation has
jumped to the insects.

10:21.922 --> 10:23.432
The mosquitoes might not be
able to distribute the cure.

10:23.456 --> 10:25.134
MITCH: It's worse than that.
What do you mean?

10:25.158 --> 10:27.227
There are five species

10:27.260 --> 10:29.096
known to be essential
to human survival:

10:29.129 --> 10:33.667
bees, bats, butterflies,
primates and plankton.

10:33.701 --> 10:35.435
We've already lost
bats and primates.

10:35.468 --> 10:37.313
MITCH: Without the insects,
the only thing we have left

10:37.337 --> 10:40.107
on our side is the oh-so-useful
plankton we're losing.

10:40.140 --> 10:41.909
Our only shot is the leopards.

10:41.942 --> 10:44.153
Can you get us another car so
we can make it to the boat?

10:44.177 --> 10:46.213
Okay, that won't be necessary.

10:46.246 --> 10:47.691
I'm sending choppers and
a team to New Brunswick

10:47.715 --> 10:49.817
to get Ms.
Campbell and the cure.

10:49.850 --> 10:51.384
I want to see.

10:51.418 --> 10:54.688
This is a military
operation, Dr. Morgan.

10:54.722 --> 10:55.889
No, you need a vet on board.

10:55.923 --> 10:56.957
The cure's in a leopard.

10:56.990 --> 10:59.927
Leopards have a very high
sensitivity to sound.

10:59.960 --> 11:01.128
A chopper's kind of loud.

11:01.161 --> 11:03.130
So if that animal is
not sedated properly...

11:03.163 --> 11:05.132
I'm talking .2
milligrams of diazepam

11:05.165 --> 11:07.968
too much or too little...
Then your cure is gonna

11:08.001 --> 11:10.403
wake up and chew somebody's
face off or they're gonna...

11:10.437 --> 11:12.472
Oh, go no further. I get it.

11:12.505 --> 11:15.342
Why do I get the sense your
passion goes past the leopard?

11:17.878 --> 11:19.022
By the way,
I'm on that chopper, too.

11:19.046 --> 11:20.914
If he goes, I go.

11:20.948 --> 11:23.851
Well,
I suppose you want on as well?

11:23.884 --> 11:25.228
I want to get this
child to its father.

11:25.252 --> 11:27.755
ABRAHAM: I think I
can help with that.

11:27.788 --> 11:29.757
You pulled her from
an urban transport.

11:29.790 --> 11:31.925
I think I can call the
station to find out

11:31.959 --> 11:33.502
where the mother and
infant were picked up.

11:33.526 --> 11:35.362
Thank you.

11:41.134 --> 11:43.203
Bring Jamie home safe.

11:46.974 --> 11:48.942
(indistinct radio chatter)

11:48.976 --> 11:51.244
President just declared
a state of emergency.

11:51.278 --> 11:52.880
He's starting
mandatory evacuations

11:52.913 --> 11:53.914
all across New England.

11:53.947 --> 11:55.482
Mandatory evacuations?

11:55.515 --> 11:57.217
But where will everybody go?

11:57.250 --> 11:59.386
Apparently the government's
setting up safe zones...

11:59.419 --> 12:01.955
Albany, Dover, Portland.

12:01.989 --> 12:03.056
Chopper's on its way.

12:03.090 --> 12:04.467
Did you install those
titanium clamps I asked for

12:04.491 --> 12:05.458
to secure the crate?

12:05.492 --> 12:07.394
Yes, sir.

12:07.427 --> 12:09.806
So you're the ones who figured
out why the animals went crazy.

12:09.830 --> 12:11.531
That would be us.

12:11.564 --> 12:13.934
Didn't think you
guys really existed.

12:13.967 --> 12:15.468
Thought you were
some urban myth.

12:17.871 --> 12:19.282
So what happens when
we get this leopard?

12:19.306 --> 12:23.143
We use its DNA to make a
cure, fix the animals.

12:23.176 --> 12:25.245
Just like that... wow.

12:25.278 --> 12:26.455
It's an honor to
serve alongside you.

12:26.479 --> 12:28.816
Oh, the honor is all ours.

12:28.849 --> 12:30.226
Well, we're still one
leopard short of a cure,

12:30.250 --> 12:31.952
so let's keep the champagne on
ice, okay?

12:31.985 --> 12:33.153
Copy that.

12:33.186 --> 12:34.297
We'll have you in the
air in two minutes.

12:34.321 --> 12:36.223
Wait here.

12:43.530 --> 12:46.166
After everything
we've been through,

12:46.199 --> 12:47.410
we're finally going to do this.

12:47.434 --> 12:50.370
We're going to get a cure.

12:51.371 --> 12:54.274
And Jamie.

12:56.376 --> 12:57.310
It's going to be okay.

12:57.344 --> 12:58.345
(growling)

12:58.378 --> 12:59.512
(rumbling and crashing)

12:59.546 --> 13:00.914
It's okay.

13:02.549 --> 13:04.517
(whining growl)

13:06.987 --> 13:09.056
(glass breaking)

13:09.089 --> 13:10.323
(whining)

13:14.394 --> 13:17.330
Just... just stay here.

13:17.364 --> 13:19.366
They're coming for you.

13:19.399 --> 13:21.301
You'll be safe here.

13:21.334 --> 13:24.371
(crunching and crashing)

13:24.404 --> 13:26.239
(barking)

13:32.279 --> 13:35.248
(indistinct radio chatter)

13:35.282 --> 13:38.385
15 minutes out from the
coordinates you gave us.

13:38.418 --> 13:42.255
(indistinct radio transmission)

13:42.289 --> 13:45.625
NAVY SEAL (over radio): Copy.
Command Five on the drop right now.

13:45.658 --> 13:47.995
(animal growling)

13:53.901 --> 13:55.102
(barking)

14:22.295 --> 14:25.198
Hey, come and get me!

14:25.232 --> 14:26.366
(bear growling)

14:27.400 --> 14:31.004
(growling and snorting)

14:36.043 --> 14:37.144
(loud pounding of hooves)

14:40.713 --> 14:43.416
(barking)

14:44.451 --> 14:47.354
TEAM LEADER: On your approach,

14:47.387 --> 14:48.655
look lively down there.

14:48.688 --> 14:50.490
Tranqs ready. No live rounds.

14:50.523 --> 14:52.059
We're coming in.

14:52.092 --> 14:53.426
Brace yourselves.

14:55.195 --> 14:58.031
(breathing heavily)

15:01.468 --> 15:04.204
(growling and barking)

15:06.406 --> 15:09.442
(growling and snorting)

15:13.180 --> 15:15.648
(indistinct yelling)

15:26.994 --> 15:28.996
Jamie!

15:31.364 --> 15:33.266
Jamie!

15:35.168 --> 15:37.037
They found a body, male.

15:37.070 --> 15:38.338
No sign of the leopard.

15:46.546 --> 15:49.449
(indistinct yelling)

15:50.450 --> 15:52.519
(growling)

15:52.552 --> 15:53.720
The leopard.

15:53.753 --> 15:55.755
MITCH: What?
(indistinct yelling)

15:55.788 --> 15:57.390
You got him?

15:57.424 --> 15:59.092
We have eyes on the target.

15:59.126 --> 16:02.162
SEAL: Any sign of the girl?

16:02.195 --> 16:03.630
SEAL 2: Negative!

16:05.665 --> 16:08.301
Jamie did this.

16:08.335 --> 16:09.536
Yes, Mitch.

16:09.569 --> 16:11.471
She was here.

16:12.672 --> 16:14.474
She was right here.

16:14.507 --> 16:15.742
Jamie!

16:17.410 --> 16:19.112
(grunts)

16:19.679 --> 16:23.350
(barking)

16:26.486 --> 16:28.155
JACKSON: Jamie!

16:28.188 --> 16:30.490
Let's go!
No, no, there's a woman here.

16:30.523 --> 16:31.734
SEAL: We've got to go.
There's a woman here.

16:31.758 --> 16:33.026
Let's roll.

16:33.060 --> 16:34.461
(growling)

16:34.494 --> 16:36.429
(indistinct yelling)

16:36.463 --> 16:38.498
Everyone fall in line.

16:38.531 --> 16:39.566
Jamie!

16:39.599 --> 16:41.168
We have to go.

16:41.201 --> 16:43.203
We have to go.
I am not leaving her here.

16:43.236 --> 16:44.537
She left that rope.

16:44.571 --> 16:46.806
That means she's still
alive, okay?

16:46.839 --> 16:49.118
She left the rope so we could
find the leopard, and we did.

16:49.142 --> 16:50.353
MITCH: We can't leave her here, okay?
ABRAHAM: We can come back

16:50.377 --> 16:51.478
and find Jamie. No, no, no.

16:51.511 --> 16:53.213
No. I'm not... I'm not leaving.

16:53.246 --> 16:54.547
I'm not leaving.

16:54.581 --> 16:55.515
What the hell are you doing?

16:55.548 --> 16:57.584
I'm not leaving without you.
I'm not leaving.

16:59.552 --> 17:00.552
(grunts)

17:07.560 --> 17:10.463
(barking and growling)

17:12.765 --> 17:15.268
(howling)

17:18.238 --> 17:19.472
Get your hands off me.

17:19.506 --> 17:21.441
I'm taking you back home to...

17:21.473 --> 17:24.377
Come on.

17:24.411 --> 17:25.444
SEAL: Fall in! Fall in!

17:25.478 --> 17:27.414
We've got to go! Come on!

17:27.446 --> 17:30.783
MITCH: We can still find
her, come on.

17:30.817 --> 17:32.552
(indistinct yelling)

17:37.190 --> 17:39.126
We did it to save your life.

17:39.159 --> 17:40.493
We can come back for Jamie.

17:40.527 --> 17:42.229
(groaning)

17:42.262 --> 17:43.563
Hey, keep your head.

17:43.596 --> 17:44.596
Keep your head.

17:47.567 --> 17:51.438
I hate you for this.

17:51.471 --> 17:54.241
(barking)

17:56.543 --> 17:59.579
(sound of helicopter overhead)

18:01.514 --> 18:04.517
(barking)

18:04.551 --> 18:07.587
(howling and whining)

18:10.857 --> 18:13.526
(barking)

18:13.560 --> 18:16.429
(growling)

18:19.266 --> 18:21.668
(snorting)

18:34.781 --> 18:39.186
