pour Ã©crire un mot â™ª

18:39.219 --> 18:41.521
â™ª Ma chandelle est morte,
je n'ai plus de feu. â™ª

18:41.554 --> 18:42.689
She's right over here.

18:42.722 --> 18:44.691
Oh, my God, Bella... Bella.

18:46.693 --> 18:47.727
(baby cooing)

18:47.760 --> 18:48.795
Hi.

18:48.828 --> 18:50.830
You're okay.

18:53.833 --> 18:55.802
Your wife was very brave.

18:55.835 --> 18:57.670
She saved your daughter's life.

18:57.704 --> 18:58.871
(baby cooing)

18:58.905 --> 19:00.907
Oh... (crying)

19:00.940 --> 19:02.309
Thank you.

19:14.821 --> 19:17.690
Excuse me.
You ran Jackson Oz's blood earlier

19:17.724 --> 19:18.925
for internal bleeding.

19:18.958 --> 19:20.793
Oz.

19:20.827 --> 19:21.961
Oh... here it is.

19:21.994 --> 19:23.463
Can I have his results?

19:23.496 --> 19:25.198
I'm his wife.

19:32.872 --> 19:34.574
You sure this is right?

19:34.607 --> 19:37.344
Yes, ma'am. Ran it myself.

19:39.011 --> 19:41.214
(cell phone ringing)

19:42.682 --> 19:44.617
Hello.

19:45.852 --> 19:48.588
Okay, I'll be right there.

19:48.621 --> 19:50.757
â™ª

19:50.790 --> 19:51.858
(low growl)

20:00.533 --> 20:01.768
Where's Jamie?

20:03.603 --> 20:04.871
Ask him.

20:09.376 --> 20:10.977
(wolves howling)

20:22.322 --> 20:23.956
There was nothing
you could do for her?

20:23.990 --> 20:25.958
We were surrounded.
Didn't look for her?

20:25.992 --> 20:27.594
It was not viable.

20:27.627 --> 20:29.429
Can you send a
team back up there

20:29.462 --> 20:31.431
to look for her, immediately?
Yes. I'm on it.

20:31.464 --> 20:33.866
I need to talk to Eleanor.

20:33.900 --> 20:35.935
Look,
I have to tell you something.

20:35.968 --> 20:37.570
I got a copy of
your blood tests.

20:37.604 --> 20:39.005
What did they find?

20:39.038 --> 20:41.040
Nothing.
You're perfectly healthy.

20:41.073 --> 20:42.475
Okay.

20:42.509 --> 20:44.411
Except your blood...

20:44.444 --> 20:45.954
You said you were a universal
donor, right?

20:45.978 --> 20:47.280
Yeah, I am.

20:47.314 --> 20:49.416
Not anymore.

20:51.584 --> 20:53.486
Uh...

20:53.520 --> 20:54.954
maybe they got it wrong.

20:54.987 --> 20:57.023
Right? Universal donor,
universal recipient...

20:59.025 --> 21:00.960
I got your medical records.

21:00.993 --> 21:02.995
You were born O-negative.

21:03.029 --> 21:04.030
But it changed.

21:04.063 --> 21:06.999
Recently.

21:09.402 --> 21:11.671
The mutation isn't
contagious, all right?

21:11.704 --> 21:13.640
It can't spread to humans.
We know that.

21:13.673 --> 21:15.908
Maybe we don't know
as much as we thought.

21:18.711 --> 21:20.813
(barking)

21:20.847 --> 21:23.716
MITCH: It's been ten minutes
since we administered the cure.

21:23.750 --> 21:26.686
It took a while for the
cure to work in Zambia, too.

21:28.355 --> 21:30.390
Not this long.

21:30.423 --> 21:32.425
(dog barking)

21:39.031 --> 21:41.000
It's not working.

21:41.033 --> 21:43.370
It works.

21:43.403 --> 21:44.804
You're doing it wrong.

21:47.073 --> 21:49.942
(barking)

21:49.976 --> 21:52.445
You! You did something wrong.

21:52.479 --> 21:53.956
Dr. Morgan,
we followed your protocols

21:53.980 --> 21:55.114
to the last detail.

21:55.147 --> 21:56.916
Dog seems to disagree.

21:56.949 --> 21:58.527
Did you verify the viability
of these stem cells?

21:58.551 --> 22:00.920
Measured 89% with
7-AAD dye exclusion.

22:00.953 --> 22:02.831
Cross-check for contamination?
Zero ppm detected.

22:02.855 --> 22:03.899
MITCH: Resuspend at
the right temperature.

22:03.923 --> 22:05.525
SCIENTIST: Obviously.

22:05.558 --> 22:06.802
Well, obviously not.
Something's wrong.

22:06.826 --> 22:07.994
You don't have clearance...

22:08.027 --> 22:09.929
MITCH: Clearance? We didn't fly

22:09.962 --> 22:10.930
around the world
for that leopard

22:10.963 --> 22:12.641
so that you textbook
hacks could screw it up.

22:12.665 --> 22:14.434
Hey, what's he gonna
do, Doc, huh?

22:14.467 --> 22:16.436
Make it not work more?
It's okay.

22:16.469 --> 22:18.471
(dog continues barking)

22:28.548 --> 22:29.816
(whispers indistinctly)

22:42.695 --> 22:44.564
(dog barking)

22:44.597 --> 22:45.932
(growling)

22:48.100 --> 22:49.101
Easy. Easy, easy.

22:49.135 --> 22:51.137
Good boy.

22:54.140 --> 22:55.575
Just drop.

22:55.608 --> 22:57.644
Come on, just drop.

22:57.677 --> 23:00.112
Just drop!

23:02.449 --> 23:04.617
This baseline heart
rate is way higher

23:04.651 --> 23:05.985
than anything we've seen before.

23:06.018 --> 23:07.454
It's like...

23:07.487 --> 23:10.457
it's like the dog's
still mutating.

23:16.128 --> 23:17.564
We're too late.

23:17.597 --> 23:19.065
Everything that we've done,

23:19.098 --> 23:20.933
all for nothing.

23:20.967 --> 23:22.001
Total waste!

23:23.503 --> 23:24.771
Wait...

23:24.804 --> 23:27.106
Get your hands off me, Kenyatta.
All right?

23:27.139 --> 23:28.207
Don't touch me,

23:28.240 --> 23:29.976
don't even think about
me, all right?

23:30.009 --> 23:30.977
We can find another way!

23:31.010 --> 23:33.480
We will not find another way!

23:33.513 --> 23:35.147
We will not find another way.

23:36.849 --> 23:38.985
This... is over.

23:39.018 --> 23:40.620
I'm done.

23:40.653 --> 23:42.555
(dog barking)

23:52.264 --> 23:54.242
ELEANOR: Believe me,
I'm just as disappointed as you are.

23:54.266 --> 23:55.835
Whatever was in the leopard

23:55.868 --> 23:57.870
when it cured the dog
in Zambia is gone.

23:57.904 --> 24:00.072
We're starting from scratch.
It's still there. Okay?

24:00.106 --> 24:03.009
The-the leopard, the cure,
was isolated for three months,

24:03.042 --> 24:04.052
showed no signs
of contamination.

24:04.076 --> 24:05.512
The cure didn't change.

24:05.545 --> 24:06.846
Then why didn't it work?

24:06.879 --> 24:08.180
I stayed down
there with the dog,

24:08.214 --> 24:09.749
looked through everything:

24:09.782 --> 24:12.184
the cure did not change.

24:12.218 --> 24:14.086
I believe the animals did.

24:14.120 --> 24:16.689
The mutation in the animals
has moved past the Mother Cell.

24:16.723 --> 24:18.525
I'm afraid that
we were too late.

24:18.558 --> 24:19.892
I think that the mutation

24:19.926 --> 24:21.861
is still mutating.

24:21.894 --> 24:23.963
Assuming you're right,
what is it you're asking for?

24:23.996 --> 24:25.532
More time.

24:25.565 --> 24:27.934
Okay, time is something
we have fairly little of.

24:27.967 --> 24:30.937
Amelia and I are...
were some of the last IADG members

24:30.970 --> 24:33.906
looking for a non-lethal
solution to the animal problem.

24:33.940 --> 24:35.642
After today's attacks,

24:35.675 --> 24:37.944
the Noah Objective
seems unstoppable.

24:37.977 --> 24:39.812
Well, we found a solution once,

24:39.846 --> 24:41.280
we can do it again.

24:41.313 --> 24:42.982
Eleanor...

24:44.951 --> 24:46.653
We will do everything we can

24:46.686 --> 24:47.887
to get ahead of this thing.

24:47.920 --> 24:49.522
All right? That dog...

24:49.556 --> 24:50.799
Probably all the
animals out there...

24:50.823 --> 24:52.191
Are still changing.

24:52.224 --> 24:54.894
Everything that we
have seen so far

24:54.927 --> 24:57.063
could just be the beginning.
I've heard this before.

24:57.096 --> 24:58.631
What do you mean?

24:58.665 --> 25:00.032
Dr. Mark Vickers.

25:00.066 --> 25:01.534
Another scientist
I'm working with.

25:01.568 --> 25:02.835
How did he put it?

25:04.070 --> 25:06.639
"The initial mutation
is just the preamble.

25:06.673 --> 25:08.675
The main event is coming."

25:10.042 --> 25:11.310
We need to talk to him.

25:11.343 --> 25:13.212
He's on a research
mission in Argentina

25:13.245 --> 25:15.715
with a team of Army Rangers,
searching for an animal

25:15.748 --> 25:17.617
with what he calls a
"phase two mutation."

25:19.686 --> 25:22.121
Then Argentina is our next stop.

25:22.154 --> 25:24.156
(birds squawking)

25:27.059 --> 25:29.095
Abby? No.

25:29.128 --> 25:31.598
Sarah? No.

25:31.631 --> 25:32.999
Michelle?

25:33.032 --> 25:35.001
Mary? Miranda?

25:35.034 --> 25:37.036
Nope, nope, no.

25:37.069 --> 25:38.938
You want to take a guess,
there, Dr. Vickers?

25:38.971 --> 25:40.640
What are we guessing?

25:40.673 --> 25:42.942
Ward's wife is nine
months pregnant.

25:42.975 --> 25:44.620
It's a girl,
but he won't tell us the name.

25:44.644 --> 25:46.145
Well, it's your guess.

25:46.178 --> 25:47.980
I've been friends
with Ward since Basic.

25:48.014 --> 25:50.683
I don't need a guess; I know.
Oh, so he told you.

25:50.717 --> 25:52.919
I didn't tell her zip.
She just thinks she knows.

25:52.952 --> 25:55.622
Oh, I know!
What's the name, then?

25:55.655 --> 25:58.124
My boy here's obsessed with
all things Harry Potter,

25:58.157 --> 26:00.627
so I'm gonna go with Hermione!

26:00.660 --> 26:02.128
Is she right, Ward?

26:02.161 --> 26:04.096
Like I said,
I didn't tell her zip.

26:04.130 --> 26:06.599
Hermione. Damn old lady name.

26:06.633 --> 26:08.167
I know what I know.

26:30.189 --> 26:31.691
Clear the area.

26:33.926 --> 26:35.337
RANGER 1: Check the river.
RANGER 2: On it.

26:35.361 --> 26:37.063
The animal we're
tracking did this?

26:37.096 --> 26:38.097
It would appear that way,

26:38.130 --> 26:39.298
but just to be sure...

26:40.432 --> 26:41.634
RANGER 1: Get that side.

26:41.668 --> 26:42.669
RANGER 2: Eyes out.

26:43.736 --> 26:46.005
RANGER 1: Clear.

26:59.018 --> 27:00.687
Yes.

27:01.754 --> 27:03.089
An animal with a phase two

27:03.122 --> 27:05.725
mutation inflicted these wounds.

27:05.758 --> 27:07.393
We're switching to live ammo.

27:07.426 --> 27:09.962
Whatever did this isn't
going down with tranqs.

27:09.996 --> 27:11.073
What? No, no, no, no, no, no.

27:11.097 --> 27:13.099
Absolutely not.

27:13.132 --> 27:14.667
This-this creature is the key.

27:14.701 --> 27:17.403
It's the pivotal link in the
next phase of the mutation.

27:17.436 --> 27:19.071
It must be captured alive.

27:19.105 --> 27:22.108
The tranquilizers
will take it down.

27:24.110 --> 27:25.044
You have orders.

27:25.077 --> 27:26.312
Yeah, to keep you alive.

27:26.345 --> 27:27.313
No, to help me

27:27.346 --> 27:28.881
capture this creature.

27:32.251 --> 27:35.121
Or do I need to call Washington?

27:36.956 --> 27:38.124
Stay with tranqs.

27:38.157 --> 27:40.693
Keep your sidearms close.

27:40.727 --> 27:42.228
RANGER 1: Staying with tranqs.

27:42.261 --> 27:42.929
RANGER 2: Roger that,
staying with tranqs.

27:42.962 --> 27:45.197
TEAM LEADER: Let's move out.

27:59.145 --> 28:02.214
ABRAHAM: We pushed our luck already
with the trip to New Brunswick.

28:02.248 --> 28:04.917
The friendly skies haven't
been so friendly to us.

28:04.951 --> 28:06.185
Hey, don't worry.

28:06.218 --> 28:07.329
Apparently,
according to Eleanor,

28:07.353 --> 28:08.487
this plane has been equipped

28:08.520 --> 28:10.256
with some sort of
countermeasures.

28:10.289 --> 28:11.257
So, they're going to try and

28:11.290 --> 28:14.260
squeeze us into a fighter jet.

28:18.931 --> 28:21.433
Looks like the skies just
got a whole lot friendlier.

28:23.269 --> 28:25.271
(Abraham laughs)

28:30.409 --> 28:32.211
This is your pilot,

28:32.244 --> 28:33.980
Greg Trotter.
Greg, this is Jackson Oz...

28:34.013 --> 28:35.281
Hey. Welcome.

28:35.314 --> 28:36.883
Abraham Kenyatta...
Hi, how are you?

28:36.916 --> 28:38.284
And Chloe Tousignant. Hi.

28:38.317 --> 28:40.452
Well, nice meeting y'all.

28:40.486 --> 28:41.888
I'm off to do preflight.

28:41.921 --> 28:43.155
Be in the air in no time.

28:43.189 --> 28:45.424
Enjoy your tour.

28:45.457 --> 28:48.194
The sleeping quarters and
the lounge are upstairs.

28:48.227 --> 28:50.129
You'll have to decide
amongst yourselves

28:50.162 --> 28:52.198
who gets the master bedroom.

28:53.933 --> 28:56.869
This kitchen is bigger than

28:56.903 --> 28:59.138
my first apartment.

28:59.171 --> 29:01.908
Vehicle bay is in the
tail and this is the lab.

29:01.941 --> 29:04.310
JACKSON: Eleanor...

29:04.343 --> 29:06.078
whose plane is this?

29:06.112 --> 29:09.048
An interested third party
who has a lot to lose

29:09.081 --> 29:10.883
if the Noah Objective
goes forward.

29:10.917 --> 29:14.153
And this third party is giving
us a ride to meet a scientist?

29:14.186 --> 29:15.826
Not giving you a ride,
giving you a plane.

29:16.522 --> 29:17.489
What's the catch?

29:17.523 --> 29:18.490
MITCH: No catch.

29:18.524 --> 29:19.525
Hey.

29:19.558 --> 29:21.027
That was the first question

29:21.060 --> 29:23.095
I asked, too.

29:23.129 --> 29:25.297
I also asked for

29:25.331 --> 29:28.067
a basketball hoop
right up there.

29:28.100 --> 29:30.078
Guess we haven't gotten
around to that one yet, huh?

29:30.102 --> 29:31.170
So, you're back?

29:31.203 --> 29:32.471
I thought you quit.

29:32.504 --> 29:34.384
Well, to be honest,
I got no place else to go...

29:35.574 --> 29:38.244
and I made a deal

29:38.277 --> 29:40.212
with our new pal, Eleanor, here.

29:40.246 --> 29:42.581
She's gonna send a
team to look for Jamie,

29:42.614 --> 29:44.917
and if they can't find her,
she's gonna send another

29:44.951 --> 29:47.486
and another and another
until we do find her.

29:47.519 --> 29:48.487
Right, Eleanor?

29:48.520 --> 29:49.555
As soon as a team

29:49.588 --> 29:51.090
becomes available,

29:51.123 --> 29:52.200
I'll dispatch them
to New Brunswick.

29:52.224 --> 29:53.592
Eleanor,

29:53.625 --> 29:55.394
thank you, truly.

29:55.427 --> 29:57.229
It's the least I can do.

29:57.263 --> 29:59.331
And thank you for
using your leverage.

29:59.365 --> 30:03.502
All right,
if I won all of you in a raffle,

30:03.535 --> 30:07.073
I'd probably give you back to
the guy who won second place.

30:07.106 --> 30:08.383
Although he probably
wouldn't want you, either.

30:08.407 --> 30:11.243
Nor would he want me,

30:11.277 --> 30:14.513
because I've been behaving
like a five-year-old.

30:14.546 --> 30:16.586
(clears throat) As to why
we're all being raffled off

30:16.615 --> 30:18.217
in the first place,
I can't really...

30:18.250 --> 30:19.551
Look, I'm...

30:19.585 --> 30:21.253
What I'm trying to say is

30:21.287 --> 30:23.555
we don't get to
choose our families.

30:23.589 --> 30:25.591
For better, for worse,

30:25.624 --> 30:27.626
we're pretty much family now.

30:27.659 --> 30:31.263
Right?

30:31.297 --> 30:33.565
We've got work to
do, so let's do it.

30:35.201 --> 30:36.568
JACKSON: And what is

30:36.602 --> 30:39.171
that work, Eleanor?

30:39.205 --> 30:40.539
Do we have an
official assignment?

30:40.572 --> 30:41.908
Stop the mutation.

30:41.941 --> 30:43.309
ABRAHAM: Oh.

30:43.342 --> 30:44.977
That's all.

30:45.011 --> 30:46.378
ELEANOR: Thanks to

30:46.412 --> 30:48.347
aggressive lobbying
by Reiden Global,

30:48.380 --> 30:51.918
the IADG is set to vote on the
Noah Objective in six weeks.

30:51.951 --> 30:54.386
If it's approved,
there will be no turning back.

30:54.420 --> 30:56.355
MITCH: Hang on a second.
Reiden Global?

30:56.388 --> 30:59.258
The biotech company that started
this whole animal mess...

30:59.291 --> 31:00.626
They still have a say in this?

31:00.659 --> 31:02.995
They offered a solution,
and people are listening.

31:03.029 --> 31:04.396
JACKSON: The Noah Objective

31:04.430 --> 31:06.398
is not a solution.

31:06.432 --> 31:08.400
It's murder. ELEANOR: We're part

31:08.434 --> 31:11.070
of a dwindling few who believe that.
The only way

31:11.103 --> 31:12.314
we're gonna convince
the others is

31:12.338 --> 31:14.006
by giving them a
viable alternative.

31:14.040 --> 31:15.574
Start in Argentina.

31:15.607 --> 31:19.111
Meet with Dr. Vickers, see if his work...
if this animal

31:19.145 --> 31:20.379
he's hunting can help you.

31:20.412 --> 31:22.448
We don't have much time.

31:25.717 --> 31:28.320
(rolling thunder)

31:30.422 --> 31:32.424
Come on in.

31:34.393 --> 31:36.028
It's clear.

31:36.062 --> 31:38.097
We're good to go.

31:38.130 --> 31:39.565
Okay, we'll bunk here tonight.

31:39.598 --> 31:42.134
Oh, wait. Look, we're so close.

31:42.168 --> 31:44.136
Trail's washed away.
Tracker's on the fritz.

31:44.170 --> 31:46.405
We'll leave at 0500.

31:46.438 --> 31:48.440
Ward, you got first watch.

31:48.474 --> 31:51.077
(thunder cracking)

31:56.215 --> 31:58.384
(indistinct chatter)

32:04.656 --> 32:07.593
MAN (on TV): We now have
confirmation from the IADG that

32:07.626 --> 32:09.495
the rumored cure has failed.

32:09.528 --> 32:11.530
And in light of the
attacks in Washington D.C.,

32:11.563 --> 32:15.167
suburbs all along the Eastern
Seaboard are being evacuated.

32:15.201 --> 32:17.336
Residents are encouraged
to take shelter

32:17.369 --> 32:20.372
in the nearest protected
city or government safe zone.

32:20.406 --> 32:22.674
I have the feeling things
are going to get worse

32:22.708 --> 32:24.410
before they get better.

32:24.443 --> 32:26.645
I need a drink.

32:38.424 --> 32:40.726
We got to the safe
zone a few hours ago.

32:40.759 --> 32:43.229
But there's a long
line for the computers.

32:43.262 --> 32:45.097
And the food.

32:45.131 --> 32:46.498
And showers.

32:46.532 --> 32:48.334
There's so many people here.

32:48.367 --> 32:50.536
And they all seem... angry.

32:50.569 --> 32:53.605
Yeah, well,
people are scared, Clem.

32:53.639 --> 32:56.308
And they're frustrated.

32:56.342 --> 32:58.410
I'm just glad you're safe...
You and your mom.

32:58.444 --> 33:00.246
And... Justin.

33:00.279 --> 33:02.148
How you feeling?

33:02.181 --> 33:04.483
I'm fine.

33:04.516 --> 33:07.153
They took Henry.

33:07.186 --> 33:08.720
Who did?

33:08.754 --> 33:12.191
The people here... in charge.

33:12.224 --> 33:16.162
They put him in the quarantine
with the other pets.

33:16.195 --> 33:20.532
Well, I'm sure they'll take good
care of him, okay? Don't worry.

33:20.566 --> 33:24.170
Do you think they'll
let me visit him?

33:26.138 --> 33:28.640
I don't think that's a good
idea, kiddo.

33:30.076 --> 33:31.510
Henry's going to be fine.

33:31.543 --> 33:34.012
Okay?

33:35.247 --> 33:36.748
Dad...

33:36.782 --> 33:38.717
when's this going to be over?

33:40.186 --> 33:42.488
Soon.

33:42.521 --> 33:45.391
How do you know?

33:45.424 --> 33:50.496
I know because I'm the one
who's gonna make it over.

33:50.529 --> 33:52.598
Here, check... check this out.

33:52.631 --> 33:55.367
Look at this.

33:55.401 --> 33:56.568
Oh.

33:56.602 --> 33:58.604
See all that?

33:58.637 --> 34:00.539
Would you believe
me if I told you

34:00.572 --> 34:02.541
I'm on an airplane right now?

34:02.574 --> 34:03.709
(laughing): Whoa.

34:03.742 --> 34:06.278
No way. Way.

34:06.312 --> 34:08.547
And I've got
everything I need here

34:08.580 --> 34:10.581
to, uh... to fix the animals.

34:10.616 --> 34:13.385
So you don't have to
worry about anything

34:13.418 --> 34:18.657
except for staying safe
and staying healthy, okay?

34:19.658 --> 34:21.260
Okay.

34:21.293 --> 34:23.161
I love you.

34:24.429 --> 34:26.598
I love you, too.

34:41.880 --> 34:47.253
I pulled a few strings...
Slightly illegal strings...

34:47.286 --> 34:49.321
And I changed your
medical records.

34:49.355 --> 34:52.324
Well, then, uh...

34:52.358 --> 34:55.561
we got nothing to worry
about, huh?

34:55.594 --> 34:59.198
We don't have to worry about
anyone else finding out.

34:59.231 --> 35:01.633
We'll keep this
between the two of us.

35:01.667 --> 35:04.703
Our little secret.

35:08.274 --> 35:10.709
(rolling thunder)

35:12.711 --> 35:15.247
(thunderclaps)

35:15.281 --> 35:16.915
JACKSON: Our little secret

35:16.948 --> 35:19.285
that what?

35:19.318 --> 35:22.854
My blood's changing?

35:22.888 --> 35:25.724
(laughing): That I'm changing?

35:27.926 --> 35:30.529
Changing into what?

35:30.562 --> 35:33.632
(thunder rumbling)

35:48.847 --> 35:51.650
Yes,
that is our current position.

35:51.683 --> 35:53.819
Well, I look forward
to their arrival.

35:53.852 --> 35:55.854
Thank you, Ms. Lewis.

35:55.887 --> 35:57.523
A team is en route to join us.

35:57.556 --> 35:59.225
WARD: Whoa, whoa, whoa.

35:59.258 --> 36:00.692
That mean our tour's extended.

36:00.726 --> 36:02.770
Above your pay grade, Ward.
I need to be home when Hermione is born.

36:02.794 --> 36:04.430
Hermione?

36:04.463 --> 36:05.697
(all laughing) She was right.

36:05.731 --> 36:06.865
I know what I know.

36:06.898 --> 36:08.567
Whatever.

36:08.600 --> 36:10.602
I need to be there.

36:10.636 --> 36:12.371
Yeah, I understand.

36:12.404 --> 36:13.739
Completely.

36:13.772 --> 36:15.874
But if you want what is
best for your daughter,

36:15.907 --> 36:20.579
for your sons, your wives,
we need to stay here.

36:20.612 --> 36:22.648
If we don't succeed here,
you don't have families

36:22.681 --> 36:23.815
to go back to.

36:23.849 --> 36:25.660
Everything will be gone.
Life as we know it will change.

36:25.684 --> 36:28.620
I am talking about the
extinction of the human race.

36:28.654 --> 36:29.855
But we can stop it.

36:29.888 --> 36:31.857
Our work here will
make it so our children

36:31.890 --> 36:33.592
have a future.

36:33.625 --> 36:36.595
They will be able to...

36:36.628 --> 36:37.863
ride bikes and play baseball,

36:37.896 --> 36:40.732
hold our hands when
we cross the street.

36:40.766 --> 36:42.734
Look, we may not be
home, but I assure you,

36:42.768 --> 36:45.304
we are on the front
lines of their future.

36:45.337 --> 36:46.805
(Vickers groans)

36:46.838 --> 36:49.308
(men talking over each
other, cocking guns)

36:49.341 --> 36:50.776
How many?

36:50.809 --> 36:52.778
Six Rangers and Vickers.

36:52.811 --> 36:54.946
(alarm blaring) Where was
their last checkpoint?

36:54.980 --> 36:56.782
A hostel ten kilometers north.

37:00.652 --> 37:02.888
Okay. Follow us.

37:02.921 --> 37:05.457
No, follow us.

37:15.501 --> 37:16.901
